# TASK.md — Copy this into your target repo and edit it

## Mission

Add input validation to the user registration endpoint so that malformed
requests return clear 400 errors instead of crashing with a 500.

## Definition of Done

- Email field rejects values without `@` and a valid domain
- Password field enforces minimum 8 characters, at least one digit
- Username field rejects empty strings and strings over 64 characters
- All validation errors return JSON with a human-readable `message` field
- Existing passing tests still pass

## Verifier Commands

```bash
# Fast check (runs in < 10s — agent uses this between edits)
python -m pytest tests/test_registration.py -x -q

# Full check (runs once before final commit)
python -m pytest --tb=short
```

## Context

- Registration handler is in `src/api/auth.py`, function `register_user`
- Pydantic is already a dependency — prefer field validators over manual checks
- Do not change the database schema
